Here are both approaches using `IQueryAttributable` on the ViewModel.

**1. Register the route** in `AppShell.xaml.cs`:

```csharp
public AppShell()
{
    InitializeComponent();
    Routing.RegisterRoute("productdetails", typeof(ProductDetailsPage));
}
```

**2. Navigate from ProductListPage** (e.g., on CollectionView `SelectionChanged`):

```csharp
// Approach A: string query parameter
await Shell.Current.GoToAsync($"productdetails?productId={selectedProduct.Id}");

// Approach B: pass the full Product object
var parameters = new ShellNavigationQueryParameters
{
    { "product", selectedProduct }
};
await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("productdetails", parameters);
```

**3. Receive on the ViewModel** â€” a single `ApplyQueryAttributes` handles both cases:

```csharp
public class ProductDetailsViewModel : ObservableObject, IQueryAttributable
{
    private string _productId;
    private Product _product;

    public string ProductId
    {
        get => _productId;
        set => SetProperty(ref _productId, value);
    }

    public Product Product
    {
        get => _product;
        set => SetProperty(ref _product, value);
    }

    public void ApplyQueryAttributes(IDictionary<string, object> query)
    {
        // Approach A: string parameter arrives as a string value
        if (query.TryGetValue("productId", out var id))
        {
            ProductId = id.ToString();
            // Load full product from a service, DB, etc.
        }

        // Approach B: complex object arrives as the original type
        if (query.TryGetValue("product", out var obj) && obj is Product product)
        {
            Product = product;
            ProductId = product.Id;
        }
    }
}
```

**4. Wire the ViewModel** on `ProductDetailsPage`:

```csharp
public partial class ProductDetailsPage : ContentPage
{
    public ProductDetailsPage(ProductDetailsViewModel vm)
    {
        InitializeComponent();
        BindingContext = vm;
    }
}
```

**Key differences:**

| | String query param | `ShellNavigationQueryParameters` |
|---|---|---|
| **Syntax** | `$"route?key={val}"` | `new ShellNavigationQueryParameters { ... }` |
| **Data types** | Strings only | Any object |
| **Serialization** | Goes through URI encoding | Passed by reference, no serialization |
| **Use when** | Simple IDs, flags, small values | Full model objects, complex data |

> **Tip:** Always `await` the `GoToAsync` call, and always use `ContentTemplate` with `DataTemplate` in your Shell XAML so pages load on demand.
